Let $G$ be a connected and reductive group over the algebraically
closed field $K$. J-P. Serre has introduced the notion of a G
completely reducible subgroup $H ⊂ G$.  In this note, we give a notion
of $G$ complete reducibility -- $G$-cr for short -- for Lie
subalgebras of $\operatorname{Lie}(G)$, and we show that if the closed
subgroup $H ⊂ G$ is $G$-cr, then $\operatorname{Lie}(H)$ is $G$-cr as
well.
